---
name: leadbay_create_custom_field
kind: tool-description
short_description: |
  Create an org-level CRM custom field for imports. Returns a mapping_value
  to pass in `mappings.fields` for leadbay_import_leads /
  leadbay_import_and_qualify.
annotations:
  readOnlyHint: false
  destructiveHint: false
  idempotentHint: true
  openWorldHint: true
---
Create an org-level CRM custom field for imports, then use the returned `mapping_value` in leadbay_import_leads / leadbay_import_and_qualify mappings. Use when the user's file contains valuable columns that do not fit Leadbay's standard fields, such as source-system deep links, source record IDs, campaign provenance, or user-requested enrichment attributes.

For HubSpot record links, prefer `type:'EXTERNAL_ID'` with `config.url_template` and import only the stable HubSpot id as the CSV value. Example: create field name 'HubSpot Contact', type 'EXTERNAL_ID', config `{url_template:'https://app.hubspot.com/contacts/<portal-id>/record/0-1/{value}'}`; then map `hubspot_id` to the returned `mapping_value`. If only a full URL column exists and the id cannot be safely extracted, use a TEXT field instead.

{{include:headers/tool-when-to-use}} after leadbay_list_mappable_fields shows no suitable existing custom field and preserving the column matters to the user's goal.

{{include:headers/tool-when-not-to-use}} for standard company/contact data that maps to LEAD_WEBSITE, LEAD_NAME, CONTACT_EMAIL, etc.; do not create custom fields for noisy scraper notes unless the user explicitly asks to preserve them.
